Catering Packages WELCOME TO Leyla 
Leyla is Charleston's premier family-owned Lebanese restaurant serving authentic Lebanese dishes in an elegant modern setting and a sophisticated atmosphere. Our extensive Middle Eastern menu offers shareable plates and a communal dining experience. With an extensive Wine and Cocktail list to choose from, you are sure to find the right pairing for your dish.

Reviews
Start stop reviews carousel 
Review by - google

Aleah G:
five star review by 
Seriously the best Lebanese food I've had in so so long!! Everything, EVERYTHING is homemade. Leyla's cooking is absolutely incredible and she uses the best quality ingredients you could find. I can't wait to come back! A true Charleston gem.

Review by - google

Denise K:
five star review by 
Wow! We are of Lebanese descent and the food was just as delicious as our grandmothers!! Some dishes were even better! One of the best meals I've ever had! The owner was so attentive and our server was wonderful! Can't wait to go back! Favorite dishes: the grape leaves, lamb shank, moussaka, baklava and pistachio ice cream!

Review by - google

Blair:
five star review by 
We went here for a Christmas Day lunch and it was delicious! Some of the best hummus I've ever had. My drink was super good and everyone was very kind. We would love to come back and try their standard menu.

Review by - google

Garrett R:
five star review by 
Easily the tastiest food I've had in South Carolina. A friend and I went in to snack on some falafel and hummus at the bar and loved it so much that we had to go for lunch the next day! This is an absolute must if you're living in Charleston or only visiting. Even if you're full, try the osmalieh for dessert. It's light and the pistachio ice cream is homemade.

Review by - google

Nanani A:
five star review by 
The meal made my tummy and heart extremely happy. It's like having a home cooked meal that you can taste the joy and all the love in each bite!
